quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Functions[/h1]

In the example below, we create the function [b]sayHello()[/b]. The opening curly brace ({) indicates that this is the beginning of the function code, while the closing curly brace (}) indicates that this is the end.
To call the function, just write its name: [code format="php" codeId="487"][b]function [/b]sayHello() {
  echo "Hello!";
}

[b]sayHello()[/b]; //call the function

//Outputs "Hello!"[/code]
